<m0>ALOU SPARKS MONTREAL<ql>
<m1><styl>vs,2<ql>
<styl>txt<ql>
<ep>
<m0>   MONTREAL (--) Moises Alou and former Miami Hurricane F.P. Santangelo hit two-run doubles in a five-run seventh inning to lift Montreal over Chicago Cubs and to its ninth straight home win.<ep>
   With Montreal trailing 3-2, Terry Adams (1-1) walked Andy Stankiewicz and Mark Grudzielanek. Mike Lansing sacrificed against Doug Jones, Henry Rodriguez was walked intentionally and Alou doubled for a 4-3 lead.<ep>
   David Segui walked and, one out later, Santangelo doubled it make it 6-3. Dave Silvestri followed with an RBI single. Rodriguez singled home a run in the eighth.<ep>
   Dave Veres (4-0) allowed two runs and three hits in two innings as Montreal won its fourth straight overall. The Expos haven't lost at home since April 18, a 9-8 defeat against Philadelphia.<ep>
   Adams was charged with two runs and did not retire a batter.<ep>
   Segui homered in the second off Steve Trachsel, but Tavo Alvarez walked Mark Grace with the bases loaded in the fifth.<ep>
   Santangelo hit a leadoff triple in the home fifth off Steve Trachsel, then hustled home with Montreal's second run on Cliff Floyd's groundout. Santangelo, filling in for injured Rondell White, scored when Floyd hit a chopper to Grace at third. Grace threw home, but Santangelo slid around catcher Brian Dorsett's tag for a 2-1 lead.<ql>
<m0>Perez out 4 months<ql>
<m1><ep>
<m0>  Montreal starter <m0>Carlos Perez<m0> <m1> <m0>underwent arthroscopic surgery on his left shoulder Tuesday and will be sidelined for about four months.<ep>
   Perez, 24, has not pitched this season. Doctors repaired a torn labrum tendon and an incomplete tear rotator cuff tear.<ql>
<m0>Around the league<ep>
<m0> <m0>(box) REDS: Reggie Sanders <m0>has been cleared to swing a bat again, an indication he could be back before the end of the month. The right fielder, who suffered a tear around a disk in his lower back while trying to make a diving catch April 12, will hit off a batting tee today and take ground balls.<ep>
